---
layout: layouts/base
---

{% from "macros.njk" import logotype, icon, script %}

<style>
  /*
    Resize all .containers, including the footer.container
    which is in the inherited base layout.
  */
  .container {
    max-width: calc(640px + 2rem);
  }
</style>

<div class="h-1 bg-indigo-600 dark:bg-indigo-400"></div>
<div class="home container shrink-0 grow">
  <header class="pt-20 pb-28 border-b">
    {{
      logotype(
        class="mb-3 -ml-1 h-6 w-auto md:h-7 md:mb-4 text-indigo-600 dark:text-indigo-300",
        attrs={ariaLabel: "thinkdev logo"}
      )
    }}
    <h1>{{ site.title }}</h1>
    <p class="mb-16">
      <b class="lead">Let's relearn the basics of programming,
      in the world's most popular language &mdash; JavaScript.<sup><a
        id="fn-jspop-ref"
        href="#fn-jspop"
        class="no-underline scroll-mt-2 px-0.5"
      >1</a></sup></b>
    </p>
    <a href="#lessons" class="inline-flex items-center no-underline text-lg">
      Skip to lessons
      {{ icon('arrow-down', class='ml-1.5') }}
    </a>
  </header>

  <main>
    <section class="py-24 border-b">
      <h2>Go beyond the language basics.</h2>
      <p>
        We'll learn the oft-taught things in programming &mdash; variables, functions, loops,
        and what have you &mdash; but we won't stop there.
      </p>
      <p>
        As developers, we also have to test our code,
        catch bugs, write documentation, and do a bunch of
        other stuff to maintain our code.
      </p>
      <p>
        We'll learn how to do these too, and we'll use some tools that make
        the process fun ðŸ˜‰.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="py-24 border-b">
      <h2>What to expect</h2>
      <p>At the end of the course, you should be able to</p>
      <ul class="list-check list-disc marker:text-green-500 marker:dark:text-green-300 marker:text-[1.2em]">
        <li>write and read JavaScript code confidently</li>
        <li>analyze and solve programming problems</li>
        <li>document, test, and debug simple programs</li>
        <li>work with the command line</li>
        <li>use some common data structures and algorithms</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="py-24 border-b">
      <h2>Our format and schedule</h2>
      <p>
        Each <a href="#lessons">lesson</a> includes a prerecorded lecture,
        slides, some practice exercises (that you should <em>really</em> attempt ðŸ‘€),
        and a supplementary article.
        The slides come in two forms: an interactive presentation that you can play
        on this site and a PDF file that you can download.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every Sunday, we'll meet on Zoom to review a lesson and do some Q&amp;A.
        Make sure you study the material before the meeting so we can have a lively discussion ðŸ™‚.
      </p>

      <div class="note note-info">
        <p>
          <strong>Tip:</strong>
          Press the question mark key (<kbd>?</kbd>) when viewing
          the interactive slides to see a list of keyboard shortcuts.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    {# TODO THIS PART #}
    <section class="py-24 border-b">
      <h2>This isn't a <q>JavaScript course</q>.</h2>
      <p>
        We'll mostly avoid things peculiar to JavaScript and rather focus more on
        the general programming topics that also apply to other languages.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="py-24 border-b">
      <h2>
        But &mdash; <em>hey!</em> &mdash; we're using JavaScript,
        so we'll still discuss its quirks ðŸ™ƒ.
      </h2>
    </section>

    <section class="py-24 border-b">
      <h2 id="lessons">The lessons so far</h2>
      <ol>
        {% for lesson in collections.all | eleventyNavigation %}
          <li><a href="{{ lesson.url | url }}">{{ lesson.title }}</a></li>
        {%- endfor %}
      </ol>
    </section>

    <footer class="py-16">
      {{
        logotype(
          class="h-auto w-3/5 mb-12 -ml-1.5 md:-ml-2 text-indigo-600 dark:text-indigo-400",
          attrs={ariaLabel: "thinkdev logo"}
        )
      }}

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2>Footnotes</h2>
        <ol id="footnoteList">
          <li id="fn-jspop" class="rounded scroll-mt-3 target:focused">
            See the <a
              href="https://insights.stackoverflow.com/survey/2021#section-most-popular-technologies-programming-scripting-and-markup-languages"
            >2021 StackOverflow Developer Survey</a>.
            <a
              href="#fn-jspop-ref"
              aria-label="Return up"
              title="Return up"
              class="no-underline inline-block"
            >
              {{- icon('arrow-up-short', width=20, height=20, class="mb-1") -}}
            </a>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2>References for the course content</h2>
        {% set bindingsLesson = collections.all | eleventyNavigation | find('title', 'Bindings again') %}
        <ul>
          <li>
            <a href="https://greenteapress.com/wp/think-python-2e/"><cite>Think Python</cite> by Allen Downey</a>.
            The book is also known by the title <i>How to Think Like a Computer Scientist</i>.
            Yes, it inspired this course's title ðŸ™‚.
          </li>
          <li>
            The <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript"><cite>MDN Web Docs</cite></a>.
            My primary reference for this course.
            It's a great place to learn JavaScript and other things web-related.
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://eloquentjavascript.net/"><cite class="quoted">Eloquent JavaScript</cite></a>.
            An introductory yet thorough book on programming in modern JavaScript.
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://tc39.es/ecma262/"><cite>The ECMAScript Language Specification</cite></a> (ECMA 262).
            The document that formally defines what the JavaScript language is.
          </li>
          <li>
            The prerelease draft of the
            <a href="https://justjavascript.com/"><cite>Just JavaScript</cite> course</a>.
            The course focuses on building a good mental model of JavaScript.
            It inspired the fifth episode of this thinkdev course,
            <a href="{{ bindingsLesson.url | url }}">{{ bindingsLesson.title or "Bindings again" }}</a>.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <p>And just for fun ðŸ˜ƒ ...</p>
      <p>
        I built this site with <a href="https://www.11ty.dev/">Eleventy</a>,
        <a href="https://tailwindcss.com/">Tailwind CSS</a>, and
        <a href="https://revealjs.com/">reveal.js</a> (for the slides),
        and hosted it on <a href="http://netlify.com/">Netlify</a>.
      </p>
    </footer>
  </main>
</div>
